[1m[31mE           (rdflib.term.URIRef('ontology://generated-from-draw-io/mock#Simcoe%20Family%20Fonds'), rdflib.term.URIRef('https://www.ica.org/standards/RiC/ontology#history'), rdflib.term.URIRef('ontology://generated-from-draw-io/mock#Custodial%20History%3A%20The%20Simcoe%20Family%20Papers%20Were%20Held%20By%20Descendants%20Of%20John%20Graves%20And%20Elizabeth%20Simcoe%20Until%20The%20Mid%20To%20Late-20th%20Century.%20Eliza%20Simcoe%2C%20The%20Eldest%20Daughter%20Of%20John%20Graves%20And%20Elizabeth%20Simcoe%2C%20Retained%20Possession%20Of%20The%20Records%20Which%20Make%20Up%20This%20Fonds%20Until%20Her%20Death%20In%201865.%20Between%201859%20And%201861%2C%20A%20Portion%20Of%20The%20Records%20Were%20Loaned%20To%20The%20Canadian%20Library%20Of%20Parliament%20For%20Arrangement%20And%20Partial%20Copying.%20On%20The%20Death%20Of%20Eliza%20Simcoe%2C%20The%20Records%20Passed%20To%20The%20Children%20Of%20The%20Reverend%20Henry%20Addington%20Simcoe%2C%20Eliza%27s%20Only%20Surviving%20Brother.%20Some%20Time%20After%20This%2C%20Part%20Of%20The%20Records%20Came%20Into%20The%20Possession%20Of%20The%20Vowler%20Family%20And%20The%20Coles%20Family%2C%20Each%20Related%20To%20The%20Simcoes%20Through%20Marriage%20To%20A%20Daughter%20Or%20Granddaughter%20Of%20Henry%20Addington%20Simcoe.%20In%20The%20Late%201940s%20Dr.%20S.%20McLaughlan%20Purchased%20The%20Records%20Then%20Held%20By%20The%20Coles%20Family%20And%20Donated%20The%20Whole%20To%20The%20University%20Of%20Toronto%20Library.%20In%201951%20The%20University%20And%20The%20Ontario%20Department%20Of%20Archives%20And%20Records%20Opened%20Negotiations%20To%20Transfer%20The%20Custody%2C%20But%20Not%20Ownership%2C%20Of%20The%20Simcoe%20Records%20To%20The%20Province.%20In%201952%2C%20An%20Agreement%20Was%20Signed%2C%20And%20The%20Simcoe%20Papers%20Were%20Transferred%20To%20The%20Archives%20Of%20Ontario%20In%20Order%20That%20They%20Might%20Be%20Preserved%20In%20More%20Appropriate%20Circumstances%20And%20To%20Ease%20Public%20Access%20To%20The%20Records.%20The%20Records%20Which%20Came%20To%20The%20Archives%20Under%20The%20Terms%20Of%20This%20Long-term%20Loan%20Agreement%20Represent%20The%20Bulk%20Of%20The%20Fonds.%20A%20Subsequent%20Purchase%20By%20The%20Archives%20Of%20Records%20And%20Artifacts%20From%20Other%20Simcoe%20Descendants%20In%201993%2C%20And%20A%20Number%20Of%20Small%20Donations%20From%20A%20Variety%20Of%20Sources%20Have%20Since%20Added%20To%20The%20Fonds.'))[0m
